 Homepage (index.html)
This page will introduce the website, which focuses on exercises for different muscle groups. It will include a brief overview of major muscle groups (chest, back, legs, arms, shoulders, core) and guide users to pages explaining both fitness content and web development concepts.

Using the Code Editor (code-editor.html)
This page will explain the code editor used during the course and how it helped build the fitness website. It will include examples such as writing exercise descriptions and organizing workout content efficiently.

HTML – Semantic Elements (semantic-html.html)
This page will explain semantic HTML elements using examples from the exercise website. It will show how sections like muscle groups and workouts are structured using tags like header, section, and article.

CSS – Layout and Responsive Design (css-layout.html)
This page will describe how CSS is used to create a clean layout for displaying exercises by muscle group. It will also explain how responsive design ensures the workout content looks good on phones, tablets, and desktops.

Accessibility (accessibility.html)
This page will explain how the exercise website is made accessible to all users. It will include examples like alt text for exercise images, readable fonts, and clear navigation for users with disabilities.

Ethical Issues in Web Development (ethics.html)
This page will discuss ethical concerns related to fitness websites, such as providing accurate exercise information and avoiding misleading health advice. It will also cover privacy and responsible content creation.

Validation for HTML and CSS Code (validation.html)
This page will explain how the code for the exercise website is validated. It will include examples of fixing errors and ensuring the site works properly across browsers.

Using Generative Artificial Intelligence (ai.html)
This page will describe how AI tools were used to help generate exercise ideas, explanations, and website content. It will also explain the importance of verifying AI-generated fitness information.
